"El Hipnotizador de Blois" (in spanish) [Ejemplo tomado de 12.4 del help, ilustrando el uso de Acciones con PNJs]The story headline is "Un ejemplo de acciones con PNJs"A person is either hypnotized or alert. A person is usually alert.Persuasion rule for asking a hypnotized person to try doing something:	persuasion succeeds.Understand "hypnotiza a [someone]" as hypnotizing.Hypnotizing is an action applying to one thing.Check hypnotizing:	if the noun is hypnotized, say "Ya está hipnotizada." instead.Carry out hypnotizing:	now the noun is hypnotized.Report hypnotizing:	say "[The noun] cae bajo tu control."Instead of waking someone hypnotized:	now the noun is alert;	say "[The noun] recobra abruptamente la conciencia."[We will learn more about check rules for other characters shortly, but the following prevents the hypnosis patient from trying to hypnotize us in turn:]Check someone hypnotizing someone:	stop the action.Maison de la Magie is a room. "A pocos pasos del Chateau de Blois -en una oscura habitación- das a los turistas tres espectáculos al día: desplegando un poder que no comprenden ni merecen."A voluntaria (f) is a woman in the Maison. "Una voluntaria del público está parada frente a ti, [if alert]esperando con cierto escepticismo a que la hipnotizes[otherwise]su rostro perdido en la hipnosis[end if]." The printed name of the voluntaria is "voluntaria del público". The description is "Una mujer suceptible y distraída." The voluntaria wears una t-shirt and una gorra.The player wears a top hat and a cape.Test me with "voluntaria, quitate la gorra / hypnotiza a voluntaria / look / voluntaria, quitate la gorra / despertar a voluntaria / voluntaria, ponte la gorra".